commitmsg:
Update serializer and socket for id-based refs and new scraper.
Add published_at to use for sort order.
Add stock feeds for new users.
Using a hash instead of full IDs. This *might* be more memory-efficient, it's certainly more predictable.
Client-side Javascript would have had a problem with unquoted strings.
Allowing the manifest to name the provider by environment.  -- This lets us have a provider for dev, testing, prod etc.
This seems more reasonable. I don't know the differences between 0.6.x builds anyway.
Moving some things around to make them more obvious.
Adding some config settings for the IRC bot.
A few packages that should be dependencies of others.
Adding the irc daemon as the "memory leak" has been fixed.
Getting rid of my "memory leak". -- It's amazing the difference a "});" can make.
Adding the beginnings of the project README.
Updating Config to allow configurable socket URL.
A ghastly commit of "stuff". Now that we bit this bullet, commits should get a lot more sane [read: frequent]
Removing crawler directory. -- It's really a scraper.
Making sure we always get the real name and correct gravatar size.
Adding durable messages to the normal stream of things.
A bit of a formatting cleanup and adding channelListReturned.
A few fixes for sidebar styling.
Adding a bit for the irc UA
Adding a hint if an error occurs.
Adding a unique sort extension for the array prototype.
Some style updates for the sidebar.
Ensuring we send a boolean value instead of null.
Adding the bug icon as standalone images
A little script that outputs PNGs as data urls.
Adding userName, displayName, portrait and profileUrl to social.ambient-notification-update
Not exiting when bugzilla bombs... it seems to like to timeout.
Adding the bugzilla poller to the feed daemon. Changing the max age of stories to one hour.
Setting the session length to 30 days.
Shunting the "durable" attribute for stories in the serializer.
Adding seen_at and durable for notifications.
Setting the topic for the contact list reset properly.
New line. Wow, what a commit.
Adding migrations script. This will get smarter than just ignoring dupe column names.

Fix for /feeds page.

From michaelrhanson

`"return" keypress in new feed input text box triggers "delete" button`

`This leads to rage.`

https://github.com/mozilla/motown/issues/14

The bot now by default attempts to reconnect every two seconds, logs an error and exits the process after 5 minutes. The upstart script will respawn the process at that point.

See https://github.com/mozilla/motown/issues/7
Keeping the session cookie around for a year.
Adding a couple more common status colors.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/michaelrhanson/motown into michaelrhanson-master

michaelrhanson's bot.js was a bit stale, but I think this captures the intent.

Conflicts:
	app/irc/bot.js
Added IRC server to IRC Bot log output
Socket & UI following the bot revamp.
Pulling javascript assets from an SSL-enabled server to avoid security errors.
A large-scale bot overhaul and some testing infrastructure for it.
Adding some new requirements for testing.
Adding a couple short notes about running a dev server.
Error of function being passed in as botid.
Adding some fancy-like logging to the social sidebar worker.js.
Removing the 'X-Powered-By' header to keep it a sekrit. (shhh)
Having story items show a pointer cursor.
Only doing whois lookup if nick is provided.
Using logger out of lib so we can control configuration of it
Exiting on disconnect. This lets upstart handle the disconnection, also we will notice them.
If the href was null previously, the element would not be returned. Now we set each on original element.

Conditionally sending story to worker.
 - Now is only done if the story did not exist in mysql
 - Renaming published event.
Checking case where user disconnects and was never properly added to connections hash.
Bit of a different approach for the IRC bot. -- Still needs some work.

A few minors:
 - Emptying contact list before update
 - refreshing sidebar every 1 second instead of 5 when not auth'd
 - removing logout button in sidebar
 - renaming logout to signout
 - showing only other users in contact list

Renaming events and queues.

 - A few fixes in the socket class
Keep the sidebar to 30 elements for now. This should keep things a bit more reasonable memory-wise.

Removing /login this redirect approach doesn't really 
work since you can't initiate browserid without a click / popups being blocked
Updating public url for new public DNS
Making sure we always get the real name and correct gravatar size.
Adding durable messages to the normal stream of things.

Setting the session length to 30 days.
Shunting the "durable" attribute for stories in the serializer.
Adding seen_at and durable for notifications.
